ced at The CW's [[Upfront (advertising)|upfront]] presentation that [[Batwoman]] would be introduced in the [[Arrowverse]] series' 2018 crossover, \"[[Elseworlds (Arrowverse)|Elseworlds]]\", which aired in December 2018, fighting alongside the other Arrowverse heroes, with [[Gotham City]] also appearing.<ref name=\"BatwomanCrossover\" /><ref name=\"ElseworldsTitle\" /> In July 2018, it was reported that the CW was planning to develop a series around the character, to air in 2019 if picked up. The series, said to only be a \"script-development deal\", was written by [[Caroline Dries]], who would also serve as an executive producer with [[Greg Berlanti]], Sarah Schecter, and the character's co-creator [[Geoff Johns]]. The series would be produced by Berlanti Productions and [[Mad Ghost Productions]] in association with [[Warner Bros. Television]].<ref name=\"BatwomanSeries\" /> The following month, Pedowitz noted the pilot would be completed \"for mid-season\".<ref name=\"PedowitzAug2018\" />\n\nIn December 2018, Dries submitted a \"strong\" script for a potential pilot episode, according to Nellie Andreeva of ''[[Deadline Hollywood]]''.<ref name=\"PilotOrderDeadline\" /> That led to the series receiving a pilot order from the CW the next month, to be considered for a series order in the [[2019\u201320 United States network television schedule|2019\u201320 television season]].<ref name=\"PilotOrderTHR\" /><ref name=\"PilotOrderDeadline\" /><ref name=\"PilotOrderEW\" /> As of April 2019, the series was considered \"a lock\" at The CW, and reportedly had a writing staff in place.<ref name=\"PilotBuzz\" /> On May 7, 2019, The CW ordered the show to series.<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\" /> On October 25, 2019, the series was picked up for a full season of 22 episodes.<ref name=\"Fullseason22\" /> On January 7, 2020, the series was renewed for a second season.<ref name=\"S2Renewal\" />\n\n=== Casting ===\nCasting for Kate Kane was expected to begin after the announcement of the intended series in May 2018,<ref name=\"BatwomanSeriesDeadline\" /> with the intention of casting an [[Coming out|out]] lesbian actress.<ref name=\"BatwomanCasting\" /> In August, [[Ruby Rose]] was cast as Kate Kane/Batwoman.<ref name=\"RoseCast\" /> In late January 2019, [[Meagan Tandy]], Camrus Johnson, and Nicole Kang were cast in the series regular roles as Sophie Moore, [[Luke Fox (character)|Luke Fox]], and Mary Hamilton, respectively.<ref name=\"TandyJohnsonKang\" /> This was followed shortly by the casting of [[Rachel Skarsten]] as Alice,<ref name=\"Skarsten\" /> [[Dougray Scott]] as Jacob Kane,<ref name=\"ScottCastSiegaDirector\" /> and Elizabeth Anweis as Catherine Hamilton-Kane.<ref name=\"Anweis\" /> On August 21, 2019, Sam Littlefield was cast in a recurring role.<ref name=\"Littlefield\" /> In July, [[Burt Ward]] was cast for the ''Batwoman'' part in the 2019 Arrowverse crossover \"[[Crisis on Infinite Earths (Arrowverse)|Crisis on Infinite Earths]]\".<ref name=\"Ward\">{{Cite web |url=https://tvline.com/2019/07/20/arrowverse-crossover-2019-burt-ward-batman/amp/ |title=Batman's Robin, Burt Ward, to Appear in This Fall's Arrowverse Crossover |date=July 20, 2019 |website=TVLine |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190827201841/https://tvline.com/2019/07/20/arrowverse-crossover-2019-burt-ward-batman/amp/ |archive-date=August 27, 2019 |access-date=October 4, 2019}}</ref> On October 4, 2019, [[Rachel Maddow]] and [[Sebastian Roch\u00e9]] were cast in recurring capacities.<ref name=\"RachelMaddow\" /><ref name=\"SebastianRoch\u00e9\" />\n\nThe casting of Rose as Batwoman was met by backlash on social media and received intense criticism.<ref name=\"Cavna\" /><ref name=\"Price\">{{Cite web |url=http://fortune.com/2018/08/13/ruby-rose-quits-twitter-batwoman-casting-backlash/ |title=Ruby Rose Quits Twitter Over 'Batwoman' Casting Backlash |last=Price, Emily |date=August 13, 2018 |website=[[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190524211521/http://fortune.com/2018/08/13/ruby-rose-quits-twitter-batwoman-casting-backlash/ |archive-date=May 24, 2019 |access-date=May 16, 2019}}</ref> DC Comics, which owns the rights to the longtime comic book superheroine Batwoman, reintroduced the character in 2006 as a lesbian of Jewish descent. Some online reactions attacked Rose for not being Jewish, while the main focus of the criticism was the assertion that the fact she identifies as [[gender fluidity|gender fluid]] made her \"not gay enough.\"<ref name=\"Price\" /> Rose left [[Twitter]] and deactivated public commenting on her [[Instagram]] account following the backlash.<ref name=\"Cavna\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/comic-riffs/wp/2018/08/13/ruby-rose-leaves-twitter-after-criticism-of-her-batwoman-casting/?noredirect=on |title=Ruby Rose Leaves Twitter After Criticism That She Isn't 'Gay Enough' for Batwoman |last=Cavna |first=Michael |date=August 13, 2018 |website=[[The Washington Post]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190725141026/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/comic-riffs/wp/2018/08/13/ruby-rose-leaves-twitter-after-criticism-of-her-batwoman-casting/?noredirect=on |archive-date=July 25, 2019 |access-date=May 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Writing ===\nThe Batwoman origin story presented in the series is adapted from the ''[[Batwoman: Elegy|Elegy]]'' comic book story arc.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/tv/story/2019-10-06/cw-batwoman-ruby-rose-supreme-court-lgbtq |title=Commentary: We need a queer Batwoman more than ever. Just look at the Supreme Court |last=Brown |first=Tracy |date=October 6, 2019 |website=[[Los Angeles Times]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191015010821/https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/tv/story/2019-10-06/cw-batwoman-ruby-rose-supreme-court-lgbtq |archive-date=October 15, 2019 |access-date=October 15, 2019}}</ref> The events up to the fourth episode predate Batwoman's appearance in \"Elseworlds\",<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/batwoman-pilot-spoilers-greg-berlanti-intv-jerusalem-conference-1202574105/ |title=Greg Berlanti Teases 'Batwoman' Pilot Timeline \u2013 INTV |last=D'Alessandro |first=Anthony |date=March 12, 2019 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191015163108/https://deadline.com/2019/03/batwoman-pilot-spoilers-greg-berlanti-intv-jerusalem-conference-1202574105/ |archive-date=October 15, 2019 |access-date=October 15, 2019}}</ref> after which the events surpass the crossover.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://comicbook.com/dc/2019/10/30/batwoman-has-now-caught-up-to-elseworlds-the-cw/ |title=Batwoman Has Officially Caught up to Elseworlds |last=Drum |first=Nicole |date=October 29, 2019 |website=ComicBook.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191108001954/https://comicbook.com/dc/2019/10/30/batwoman-has-now-caught-up-to-elseworlds-the-cw/ |archive-date=November 8, 2019 |access-date=November 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\nProduction on the pilot episode began on March 4 and concluded on March 25, 2019, in [[Vancouver, British Columbia]].<ref name=\"PilotProductionDates\" /><ref name=\"PilotFilming\" /> Additional filming took place in [[Chicago, Illinois]].<ref name=\"ChicagoFilming\" /> [[David Nutter]] had been chosen to serve as director and executive producer on the pilot in January 2019,<ref name=\"PilotOrderTHR\" /> but by mid-February, left the project for personal reasons. Nutter remained an executive producer on the episode, with [[Marcos Siega]] replacing him as director and also serving as an executive producer.<ref name=\"ScottCastSiegaDirector\" /><ref name=\"Anweis\" /> Filming for the rest of the season began on July 4 and was set to conclude in mid-2020.<ref name=\"S1ProductionDates\" /> On March 12, 2020, Warner Bros. Television shut down production on the series due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref name=\"Productionshutdown\"/>\n\n== Release ==\n=== Broadcast ===\nThe series debuted on October 6, 2019.<ref name=\"SeriesPremiereDate\" /> In New Zealand, the series is streamed on [[TVNZ]]\u2019s free streaming streaming service [[TVNZ OnDemand]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.tvnz.co.nz/what-to-watch/news-feed/tvnz-highlights--5-11-october |title=TVNZ Highlights: 5\u201311 October |publisher=[[TVNZ OnDemand]] |access-date=November 23, 2019}}</ref> In the United Kingdom, the series is shown on [[E4_(TV_channel)|E4]].<ref>https://www.geektown.co.uk/tvairdates/batwoman/</ref>\n\n=== Marketing ===\nOn May 16, 2019, The CW released the first official trailer for the series.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/video/batwoman-trailer-first-look-ruby-rose-cw-series/ |title='Batwoman' Trailer: First Look At Ruby Rose In CW Series |last=Petski |first=Denise |date=May 16, 2019 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190516183615/https://deadline.com/video/batwoman-trailer-first-look-ruby-rose-cw-series/ |archive-date=May 16, 2019 |access-date=May 16, 2019}}</ref> The trailer received a negative reaction on [[YouTube]], with viewers accusing it of an overemphasis on [[feminism]].<ref name=\"CB\" /><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cbr.com/batwoman-trailer-comment-bombing-youtube/ |title=Batwoman Trailer Suffers Massive Comment Bombing on YouTube |last=Nolan |first=L.D. |date=May 19, 2019 |website=[[Comic Book Resources]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190524213518/https://www.cbr.com/batwoman-trailer-comment-bombing-youtube/ |archive-date=May 24, 2019 |access-date=May 22, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"TDD\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.dailydot.com/irl/batwoman-trailer/ |title=No one is happy about the 'Batwoman' show\u2014but there's more to it than sexism |last=Dalbey |first=Alex |date=May 17, 2019 |website=[[The Daily Dot]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190522001315/https://www.dailydot.com/irl/batwoman-trailer/ |archive-date=May 22, 2019 |access-date=May 22, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://wegotthiscovered.com/tv/batwoman-trailer-hits-170k-dislikes-fans-lash-show/ |title=Batwoman Trailer Hits 170K Dislikes As Fans Lash Out At The Show |last=Joseph |first=Matt |date=May 19, 2019 |website=We Got This Covered |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190613110715/https://wegotthiscovered.com/tv/batwoman-trailer-hits-170k-dislikes-fans-lash-show/ |archive-date=June 13, 2019 |access-date=May 22, 2019}}</ref> The trailer received 86,000 \"likes\" compared to 428,000 \"dislikes\" by August 22, 2019. ''Comic Book''  compared the backlash against a perceived agenda to that suffered by 2019's ''[[Captain Marvel (film)|Captain Marvel]]'' and its actress [[Brie Larson]].<ref name=\"CB\">{{Cite web |url=https://comicbook.com/dc/2019/05/21/batwoman-trailer-hit-comment-bombing-downvoting-youtube/ |title=Batwoman Trailer Hit by Comment Bombing, Downvoting on Youtube |last=Schmidt |first=JK |date=May 21, 2019 |website=Comicbook.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190524221908/https://comicbook.com/dc/2019/05/21/batwoman-trailer-hit-comment-bombing-downvoting-youtube/ |archive-date=May 24, 2019 |access-date=May 21, 2019}}</ref> Alex Dalbey of ''[[The Daily Dot]]'' noted how the trailer received a range of angry reactions, but nonetheless felt that criticism of the trailer's focus on the protagonist being a woman was valid, which she found to be \"forced\" and \"hamfisted\" via the dialogue and choice of song. Dalbey also wrote: \"It's 2019; we have [[Wonder Woman]], [[Black Widow (Natasha Romanova)|Black Widow]], [[Supergirl (Kara Zor-El)|Supergirl]], [[Jessica Jones]], [[Spider-Woman (Gwen Stacy)|Spider-Gwen]], [[Carol Danvers|Captain Marvel]] and more. Batwoman isn't even the first lesbian superhero on the CW, there's also [[Thunder (comics)|Thunder]] in ''[[Black Lightning (TV series)|Black Lightning]]''.\"<ref name=\"TDD\" /> However, Jean Bentley of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' noted, \"The character of Batwoman, aka Batman's cousin, Kate Kane, is the first lesbian superhero to headline her own series.\"<ref name=\"Bentley\">{{Cite news |last=Bentley |first=Jean |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/ruby-rose-batwoman-1229120 |title='Batwoman' Star Ruby Rose Hopes Groundbreaking Lesbian Superhero Appeals to Everyone |date=August 4, 2019 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=October 7, 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191007052626/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/ruby-rose-batwoman-1229120 |archive-date=October 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n===Ratings===\n{{Television episode ratings\n| width     = 99\n| title1    = [[#ep1|Pilot]]\n| date1     = October 6, 2019\n| rs1       = 0.5/2\n| viewers1  = 1.86<ref name=\"1.01\" />\n| dvr1      = 0.3\n| dvrv1     = 0.99\n| total1    = 0.8\n| totalv1   = 2.85<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/live7-ratings-week-of-sept-30-evil-stumptown-emergence-1203371610/ |title=Live+7 Ratings for Week of Sept. 30: 'Evil,' 'Stumptown,' and 'Emergence' All Double |last=Thorne |first=Will |date=October 15, 2019 |website=Variety |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191015210617/https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/live7-ratings-week-of-sept-30-evil-stumptown-emergence-1203371610/ |archive-date=October 15, 2019 |access-date=October 15, 2019}}</ref>\n\n| title2    = [[#ep2|The Rabbit Hole]]\n| date2     = October 13, 2019\n| rs2       = 0.3/1\n| viewers2  = 1.45<ref name=\"1.02\" />\n| dvr2      = 0.4\n| dvrv2     = 1.00\n| total2    = 0.7\n| totalv2   = 2.45<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/live7-ratings-for-week-of-oct-7-this-is-us-masked-singer-1203379328/ |title=Live+7 Ratings for Week of Oct. 7: 'This Is Us' Overtakes 'Masked Singer' |las