 to save her before arresting her. Disgusted by what August did to Beth and her mother, Kate accidentally strangles him, much to Jacob's dismay as he returns with Alice. Kate secludes herself and starts drinking.\n |LineColor       = 762C2A\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 16\n |Title           = Through the Looking-Glass\n |DirectedBy      = [[Sudz Sutherland]]\n |WrittenBy       = Nancy Kiu\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|22}}\n |ProdCode        = T13.21966\n |Viewers         = 0.77<ref name=\"1.16\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-sunday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-22-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Sunday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.22.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=March 24, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Jacob buries August's body and reluctantly lets Beth go. Arriving at the Wonderland Gang's hideout hoping to find Mouse, Alice instead finds her gang dead, so she ropes Kate into helping her find Mouse and the gang's killer. They visit a nurse who treated Mouse, only to find the Crows taking him to Arkham. Following a disagreement and fight, Kate agrees to help Alice break him out. They retrieve the keys to Mouse's cell, but when Alice goes to free him, Kate locks her in with him before revealing she was part of a sting operation with Jacob to capture her. Meanwhile, Jacob instructs Sophie to investigate Lucius' death after hearing of Reggie's re-trial. While doing so, a sniper nearly kills her, but Julia saves her. Elsewhere, Luke and Mary attend Reggie's court hearing, where he is granted his re-trial and released. Luke confronts him, but Reggie claims he was set up before he's mysteriously shot. Sophie later calls Jacob to inform him that two people connected to the case have turned up dead before the hitman nearly kills him, though Jacob's able to defeat him. When he interrogates him for answers however, the hitman